<span id="freeTextContainer14656391037888419684">This intriguing story is a slow build. Lachlan takes over his father’s company when he succumbs to cancer but everything is a mess. Brittney who was his father’s right arm woman is the CFO and there lies the problem because she and his father were into all kinds of schemes that backfired upon his illness. When the assistant catches Lachlan’s eye, Brittney makes her job a living hell. Lachlan is trapped because if he turned them in his sick father goes to jail. All of this is just one aspect but </span>
  <span id="freeText14656391037888419684" style="display:none">This intriguing story is a slow build. Lachlan takes over his father’s company when he succumbs to cancer but everything is a mess. Brittney who was his father’s right arm woman is the CFO and there lies the problem because she and his father were into all kinds of schemes that backfired upon his illness. When the assistant catches Lachlan’s eye, Brittney makes her job a living hell. Lachlan is trapped because if he turned them in his sick father goes to jail. All of this is just one aspect but as the layers come unraveled, there is so much more happening in this story that keeps you glued to all the drama. I voluntarily agreed to receive an ARC of this book for an honest review.</span>
