    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3885654583" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3885654583" />
    <a title="Jessica Hawkins" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/104931909-jessica-hawkins"><img alt="Jessica Hawkins" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1595969464p2/104931909.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3885654583?book_show_action=true">Mar 11, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jessica Hawkins" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jessica Hawkins" href="/user/show/104931909-jessica-hawkins">Jessica Hawkins</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/57131254-a-taste-of-peace">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3885654583" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14369959796333210837">This was so good! I just finished reading this and I couldn’t put it down. I really enjoyed this book. It had just enough of everything! This book follows Miranda Flowers as she navigates a whole new life, from her new job, to her first romance, to a whole new outlook on everything. Lachlan Peace is experiencing new things as well as he moves away from his bad boy ways for the straight and narrow path. He’s learning that his life is riddled with some bad decisions, not all his own making, but he</span>
  <span id="freeText14369959796333210837" style="display:none">This was so good! I just finished reading this and I couldn’t put it down. I really enjoyed this book. It had just enough of everything! This book follows Miranda Flowers as she navigates a whole new life, from her new job, to her first romance, to a whole new outlook on everything. Lachlan Peace is experiencing new things as well as he moves away from his bad boy ways for the straight and narrow path. He’s learning that his life is riddled with some bad decisions, not all his own making, but he’s trying to make things right. They learn and grow together. <br /><br />Miranda was a great character, maybe slightly naive but she really comes out of her shell. For being thrown into all these high end new experiences, she handles herself really well and it’s easy to see how that can be attractive to a bad boy billionaire Lachlan. I like that her character brings out a whole new side of him. They’re each experiencing something new and I’m looking forward to the next book to see where they end up. I enjoyed the sisterly bond, the close friends of Lachlan, the music and art aspects as well. There’s quite a bit of drama and conflict that moved the story along really well. This book was quite scandalous too, Miranda and Lachlan have chemistry and great spicy scenes but there’s also some hints at really dark and scandalous stuff. Overall a great read! Would definitely recommend and I’m so very looking forward to the next book in the series! <br /><br />I voluntarily reviewed this after receiving a free copy. </span>
  <a data-text-id="14369959796333210837" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


