  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3855658164" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3855658164" />
    <a title="Grady" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1362506-grady"><img alt="Grady" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442472304p2/1362506.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3855658164?book_show_action=true">Feb 23, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Grady" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Grady" href="/user/show/1362506-grady">Grady</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3855658164" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13638324116024331937">‘I liked her. She was calming….’ – A new challenging romance!<br/><br/>Australian author J.J. Sorel earned a certificate in Writing Romance with the Australian College of Journalism and began to follow her passion – writing steamy contemporary romance novels of the sort that entice those who love the Chick Lit genre. Her novels to date – THORNHILL TRILOGY, BEAUTIFUL BUT STRANGE TRILOGY, THE IMPORTANCE OF BEING BELLA, THE IMPORTANCE OF BEING WILD, TAKE MY HEART, and now this fresh new MALIBU SERIES of whic</span>
  <span id="freeText13638324116024331937" style="display:none">‘I liked her. She was calming….’ – A new challenging romance!<br /><br />Australian author J.J. Sorel earned a certificate in Writing Romance with the Australian College of Journalism and began to follow her passion – writing steamy contemporary romance novels of the sort that entice those who love the Chick Lit genre. Her novels to date – THORNHILL TRILOGY, BEAUTIFUL BUT STRANGE TRILOGY, THE IMPORTANCE OF BEING BELLA, THE IMPORTANCE OF BEING WILD, TAKE MY HEART, and now this fresh new MALIBU SERIES of which A TASTE OF PEACE Is Book1. Most of her books are available in Spanish as well as English!<br /><br />One of the reasons JJ’s novel A TASTE OF PEACE is so successful is her fine tuned sense of character development. She creates characters that are wholly credible - an example is her upfront introduction of Miranda: “My cell phone pinged with a message from Britney Gane. She’d interviewed me for a job as an administrative assistant and was the CFO to Peace Holdings, a property development firm, run by billionaire Lachlan Peace. The position seemed straight-forward enough. I just had to do what she told me…’ Then we meet Lachlan, when Britney introduces Miranda – ‘Britney looked at me as though I’d asked her to swim in a tank full of sharks, …One of the biggest downsides to running a billion-dollar empire were the endless charity balls I was forced to attend, not to mention the many advances that sashayed my way…’ The manner in which JJ interweaves these disparate types is what makes the novel ring true.<br /><br />The synopsis is seductive – ‘Reformed bad boy, and musician, Lachlan Peace finds himself running his dying father’s empire. It’s not just the shady schemes that his father set up that’s got him all hot and flustered, but also his curvy new admin assistant, Miranda. But there are endless obstacles, one of which involves his right-hand woman. Possessing all kinds of nasty secrets, she wants Lachlan Peace for herself..’<br /><br />This is one finely scribed novel that is rich in steamy erotica and yet goes beyond the usual Chick Lit realm because of the fine character flaws that tie it together. JJ Sorel continues to prove her major status as a romance author. Recommended.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13638324116024331937" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

