<span id="freeTextContainer14168447569894321316">This was my first time reading something by JJ Sorel, but won&apos;t be my last. A Taste of Peace grabbed my attention from the beginning and never let go. Thanks to Hidden Gems I was able to read straight through from A Taste of Peace to Devoured by Peace so I was able to get the whole story. As another reviewer mentioned, the ending of book one left you wanting more of their story. with the ending a bit abrupt. Lachlan and Miranda have undeniable chemistry from the beginning, but with so many force</span>
  <span id="freeText14168447569894321316" style="display:none">This was my first time reading something by JJ Sorel, but won't be my last. A Taste of Peace grabbed my attention from the beginning and never let go. Thanks to Hidden Gems I was able to read straight through from A Taste of Peace to Devoured by Peace so I was able to get the whole story. As another reviewer mentioned, the ending of book one left you wanting more of their story. with the ending a bit abrupt. Lachlan and Miranda have undeniable chemistry from the beginning, but with so many forces working against them you're left wondering whether they can possibly have a HEA. Lachlan's dad leaves MUCH to be desired, as does Britany and his step-mother. Throw in a less than scrupulous art dealer and things really get crazy. All the while, Miranda is trying to find her way in the world of art while dealing with her very strong feelings for Lachlan. This story is definitely for the 18+ audience. Looking forward to reading Ollie and Harriet's story next.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14168447569894321316" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
